trust law have interacted in the digital age. “This book will become the gold standard for analysis of the monopolization cases against Microsoft. . . . No serious student of law or economic policy should go without reading it.”—Thomas C. Arthur, Emory University  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh  amicrosoft, consumer welfare, technology, innovation, antitrust, monopoly, personal computers, litigation, sherman act, java, exclusive contracts, market division, remedies, integration, middleware, operating systems, software, liability, european commission, nonfiction, law, legal, history, business, capitalism, regulation, government.1 aLopatka, John E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022664463940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226644653423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226644653/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles